  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Fortunella is run by the Sorrentino family and there's a really friendly feel about the place. It's just two minutes from the beach in Lido di Camaiore on the <a data-udi="umb://document/56a6c9526dcb4eada10b90c88147868c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56a6c9526dcb4eada10b90c88147868c}" title="Tuscany Coast">Tuscan Coast</a>. Here you can make the most of the sun and sea, whilst being close to Tuscany's stunning sights. The waterfront promenade has a lively atmosphere, with lots of restaurants, cafe's and bars to choose from. On the other side of the promenade you'll find the sandy beach and plenty of colourful parasols and sun loungers (payable locally), so you can relax beneath the Tuscan sun. When you're not on the beach there's lots of space to chill out in the hotels gardens - you could even treat yourself to a refreshing Aperol spritz from the bar. </p>
<p><span>Inside, the building's modern and bright. We love that all of the rooms have balconies, and whats even better are the sea or mountain views you get from them. In the restaurant the food's delicious - it's some of the best home cooked meals we've had in Italy. If you upgrade to half board you'll get to try the beautiful Tuscan dishes, made with fresh local ingredients, every night. </span></p>
<p>Whether you want to see the leaning tower in Pisa, the beautiful marble of Carrara or wander through the Renaissance city of Florence, you'll find them all within easy reach. Its perfectly situated to get around by public transport, by bus or by train from Viareggio. The staff will give you some great recommendations and help you work out the best routes if you fancy a day trip. Walker's will love being so close to the Apuan Alps too. They'll become the backdrop to your holiday - you can even see the mountains from some of the rooms. </p>
<p><span>Transfer time: approx. 35 mins by private car from Pisa airport.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
